<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.65.20a-20b_0001a" />

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street
Lincoln, Neb
86505<sic>68505</sic>  
3-5-'73
</dateline>

<salute>Dear Lucile 
and Bower:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I've <hi rend="underline">just read</hi> about your retirement, Bower, and I congratulate you, and <unclear>cynic</unclear>, for I know what a lot of work you have to do. I wish you <hi rend="underline">Good Hunting</hi>! And Lucile, I'm seem a nature, endemically

<pb facs="nei.j4c.65.20a-20b_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial"><unclear>-2-</unclear></fw>

scattered all over the country, about your volume of my letters! I wonder if you have a publisher yet &#8212; ?</p>

<p>Busy doings here. United Artists is here with the sound truck, making master tapes of my poetry. We have thus far done 22 poems. It's a big project &#8212; <del/> 8 or 10 <del/> <hi rend="underline">albums</hi>. There will be a first edition of 20,000 copies of each album. We finished <hi rend="underline">The Stranger at the Gate</hi>

<fw type="curatorial">20a</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.65.20a-20b_0002a"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

yesterday. The plan is to go on with <hi rend="underline">all</hi> my work, including all <unclear>press</unclear>!!</p>

<p>They are taking <unclear>supplemented</unclear> sounds from the Missouri River already for <hi rend="underline">The River and I</hi>. There are Neihardt fans, and really enthusiastic. This issue of 20,000 albums will be great publicity for <hi rend="underline">you</hi> too.</p>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.65.20a-20b_0002b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-4-</fw>

<p>Excuse my writing. I <del/>used to write <unclear>it</unclear> all.</p>

<p>I'm coming on with the <unclear>new</unclear> book. "All is But a <hi rend="underline">Beginning</hi>" is in the 4th printing, maybe the fifth by now. <unclear>People all over the specialty really like it</unclear> <hi rend="underline">When The Tree Flowered</hi> is also going to town.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Love to each of you.</salute>

<signed>&#8212; <hi rend="underline">Gaki</hi></signed>
</closer>

<fw type="curatorial">20b</fw>

</div1>
